The paper focuses on optimizing cache performance for graph analytics, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The techniques presented in the paper are applicable to a wide range of graph applications, making it relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of various graph algorithms, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and performance (cs.PF) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents techniques that can be implemented on top of existing graph frameworks, which is relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
